# Realtime Architecture (EPIC 4)

- Keep WebSockets in `apps/realtime` (never inside `apps/api`).
- `apps/api` publishes domain events; `apps/realtime` consumes and broadcasts.
- Do not import internal code across apps; share contracts via `packages/*`.

# Auth & Connectivity

- Authenticate WebSocket in the Socket.IO handshake and attach user to
  `socket.data.user`.
- Support `AUTH_MODE=local` (JWT_SECRET) and `AUTH_MODE=keycloak` (JWKS).
- Do not enforce `issuer` in local dev; Keycloak host differs in containers.

# Realtime Events

- Room naming: `ticket:{id}`.
- Event names: `message:new` (from `message.sent`), `ticket:statusChanged`
  (from `ticket.status_changed`).
- Room access mirrors API ownership rules (`admin`/`agent` any ticket, `customer`
  only own tickets).

# Messaging Reliability

- RabbitMQ connections must use retry/backoff on startup.
- Avoid crashing realtime when RabbitMQ is temporarily unavailable.

# Testing Expectations

- Use fresh tokens for REST calls (expired tokens yield 401).
- Debugging WebSocket issues:
  - `xhr poll error` -> realtime not on port 3002
  - `Invalid token` -> token expired or auth mode mismatch
